                        Fronttalk Defines:  BULLMSG

Usage:  DEFINE BULLMSG "<string>"

The BULLMSG define is used to generate the output from the "DISPLAY BULL"
command.  (Note that the LINMSG also displays the bulletin file.)

For full details on its format, see help pages on SEPARATORS, CONFFUNC,
CONFCOND, and SEPDATE.

The default value is:

   "%(1x%3g%)%c"
